<div class="tip_number">TIP 171</div>
<div class="tip_contents">
            On rare occasions certain medications can cause fatal reactions, starting with a rash with targetlike lesions. This distinctive symptom is usually accompanied by sores in the mouth, nose, eyes, anus, and/or genital region, and a low-grade fever. Though extremely dangerous, this condition is treatable and curable if caught early.
        </div>

